data.meta_description: The John F. Kennedy Pavilion, built at a cost of $1.1 million and completed in 1965, boasted two gymnasiums, an Olympic-size swimming pool, multiple exercise rooms, and a basketball court with seating for 3,800 spectators. In 1986, after a significant expansion, the Kennedy Pavilion was renamed the Martin Centre for the project's principal donor, Charlotte Y. Martin.
